Bubble Sort Algorithm is an algorithm used to sort array elements by comparing with adjacent elements.
Best Case Time Complexity O(n)
Worst Case Time Complexity O(n2)

ALGORITHM:-
==> Run the loop from elements in array
==> For every element compare with previous and current element
==> if element is smaller than swap the elements


[Note for every iteration, largest element will move to the end of the array with respective index.]


ALGO:=
import java.util.*;
public class Main {  
    public static void main(String args[]){
    int arr[]={5,1,2,4,3};
     bubbleSort(arr);
    }
    public static void bubbleSort(int arr[]){
      //Run the loop for n-1 steps
      for(int i=0;i<arr.length;i++){
        //For each step, max value will come at last respective Index
        for(int j=1;j<arr.length-i;j++){
          //Swap elements if current elements is smaller than previous elements
          if(arr[j] < arr[j-1]){
            int temp=arr[j];
            arr[j]=arr[j-1];
            arr[j-1]=temp;
          }
        }
      }
    }
}
